Reasoning: The paper deals with the Blahut Arimoto algorithm, which is a well-known algorithm in information theory for computing the capacity of discrete memoryless channels. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also provides a geometrical interpretation of the algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). Additionally, the paper proposes an improved version of the algorithm, which may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence rate of the algorithm, which may also place it under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
